Hung Hsiu-chu, former chairperson of the Chinese Kuomintang party, will lead a delegation of personages from various circles in Taiwan to visit Beijing from May 12 to 15, a Chinese mainland spokesperson said Thursday.People from both sides of the Taiwan Strait will conduct consultations on issues of common concern such as cross-Strait relations and the future of the Chinese nation, said Ma Xiaoguang, a spokesperson with the State Council Taiwan Affairs Office."The mainland will work with people of insight from all walks of life on the island to advance cross-Strait relations in the right direction, create a better future for cross-Strait relations, and share the glory of the rejuvenation of the Chinese nation," Ma said. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Delegation of HUST attends alumni gala in Los AngelesChinese driving Vegas growthHaving fun